===Etymology===
Arabic {{ARchar|[[اسلام|إسْلام]]}} (''‘islām'') "submission" (to the will of God). The root is the same as that of {{ARchar|[[سلام|سَلام]]}} ("salām"), "peace".

===Noun===
'''Islam'''
{{wikipedia}}
# A [[monotheistic]] [[religion]] founded by Prophet [[Muhammad]] (SAW) having the same [[root]]s as [[Christianity]] and [[Judaism]]; its [[revelatory]] [[scripture]] is the [[Qur'an]]; its [[follower]]s are [[Muslim]]

